B.a9F=new A.k_("Grade 3+ Positive Sharp Waves","When denervation is severe, you don't just see a few blips. You see abundant positive sharp waves filling the screen across multiple muscle areas. This signifies a structurally significant nerve injury.","fT6Lx4rnRNs",B.Ym)
B.LW=new A.cq("The Sound","An incredibly distinctive, perfectly regular 'machine-like' or 'idling motorcycle' sound.")
B.M5=new A.cq("The Look","Multi-serrated, complex spikes that are completely uniform from discharge to discharge.")
B.M9=new A.cq("The Rate","Typically 5-100Hz. The key is that they are *perfectly* regular, unlike fibs which are semi-rhythmic.")
B.LQ=new A.cq("The Mechanism","Ephaptic transmission. One denervated fiber acts as a pacemaker, triggering adjacent denervated fibers in a closed loop.")
B.Y9=s([B.LW,B.M5,B.M9,B.LQ],t.LK)
B.a9H=new A.k_("Complex Repetitive Discharges (CRDs)","These sound exactly like a perfectly tuned engine. What you're seeing are individual muscle fibers that are time-linked, firing in an ephaptic loop. We see this in chronic, long-standing neuropathic or myopathic conditions.","UE-UIRDzZ-U",B.Y9)
B.M8=new A.cq("The Sound","A rhythmic, rhythmic bursting. 'Marching soldiers' hitting the pavement.")
B.Mh=new A.cq("The Look","Grouped, repetitive discharges of the exact same Motor Unit Action Potential (MUAP).")
B.LP=new A.cq("The Rate","Interburst frequency is 1-5Hz; intraburst frequency is 5-60Hz.")
B.LJ=new A.cq("Key Associations","Radiation plexopathy (very common), Multiple Sclerosis (if facial), Guillain-Barr\xe9, or chronic compressive neuropathy.")
