c1=A.cf(A.a([],m),c2,c1)
b8=A.cd("Charcot-Marie-Tooth Disease Type 1 (CMT1)",c0,k0,"INDICATED (Uniform vs Multi-focal)",A.a([A.z(!0,f0,f0,f0,f0,h3,g9,h0,f0,h4,h1,f0),A.z(!0,f0,f0,f0,f0,h3,h5,h6,f0,h4,h1,f0),A.z(!0,"Chronic neurogenic changes",f0,f0,f0,h3,l5,l6,f0,h4,q4,f0),A.z(!0,f0,f0,f0,f0,h3,m4,m5,f0,h4,m6,f0),A.z(!1,"Proximal sparing",f0,f0,f0,f0,m7,m8,f0,f0,m9,f0)],n),"Classic hereditary demyelinating polyneuropathy (likely PMP22 duplication). Hallmark is uniform, symmetric, and severe slowing of conduction velocities across all nerves and segments (typically 15-25 m/s) without evidence of conduction block or temporal dispersion. Clinical markers like Pes Cavus and family history are highly supportive.",b9,"cmt",c1,ae7,ae6,!0,b8,A.a(["Charcot-Marie-Tooth (CMT) Type 1 is the most common hereditary polyneuropathy.","NCS hallmark: Uniform and symmetric conduction velocity slowing across all nerves and segments, with no evidence of conduction block or temporal dispersion.","Motory velocities in CMT1 are typically <30 m/s (mean ~20 m/s).","Clinical clues include high arches (Pes Cavus), hammer toes, and distal leg atrophy ('inverted champagne bottle').","Inheritance is usually Autosomal Dominant, with PMP22 duplication being the most common genetic cause."],af2),"Life-long Difficulty Walking and High Arches")
ae6=A.cc(45,"Severe burning pain and 'electric shocks' in the soles of both feet",d5,"45-year-old female with a 3-month history of progressive burning pain in her feet. The pain is worse at night and sometimes feels like 'walking on glass'. She denies any weakness, balance issues, or back pain. She has recently started a lifestyle program for pre-diabetes.","Lisinopril","Retail Manager","Pre-diabetes (A1c 6.2%), Hypertension")
ae7=A.cg("Normal muscle bulk in all 4 limbs. No skin changes, rashes, or ulcers on the feet.","No muscle tenderness. No spinal tenderness.","2+ and symmetric Patellar and Achilles reflexes. Babinski is negative.",v3,"Decreased pinprick and temperature sensation in a stocking distribution up to the ankles. **Vibration, Proprioception, and Light Touch are entirely normal.**","Gait: Normal, including heel-to-toe walk. Romberg: Negative.","5/5 strength throughout, including intrinsic foot muscles and ankle dorsiflexion/plantarflexion.")
c1=A.a([A.V(ac6,d9),A.V("Large Fiber Polyneuropathy","Large fiber involvement would typically show abnormal vibration/proprioception, absent reflexes, and abnormal NCS (low amplitudes or slow velocities); here all are normal."),A.V("Erythromelalgia","Characterized by episodic redness and warmth in addition to burning pain; here there are no visible skin changes or color changes."),A.V(ac7,"Pain is typically worse with the first steps in the morning and localized to the calcaneal insertion; here it is diffuse, burning, and nocturnal."),A.V("L5-S1 Radiculopathy","Would be asymmetric, usually involve back pain, and often show reflex/strength changes; here it is symmetric and distal.")],ae8)
b9=A.a4(["constitutional",u6,"musculoskeletal","Burning feet. No joint pain.","neurological","Painful sensory symptoms. No weakness. No hand symptoms."],af0,af0)
