c0=A.cd(ac8,c2,k0,e2,A.a([A.z(!0,f0,f0,h2,f0,l9,"Abductor Hallucis","Medial plantar",f0,h4,m6,f0),A.z(!0,f0,f0,h2,f0,l9,"Abductor Digiti Quinti (Foot)","Lateral plantar",f0,h4,m6,f0),A.z(!1,h7,f0,f0,f0,f0,l5,l6,f0,f0,l7,f0),A.z(!1,h7,f0,f0,f0,f0,m0,l6,f0,f0,m1,f0),A.z(!1,h7,f0,f0,f0,f0,m2,q7,f0,f0,m1,f0),A.z(!1,h7,f0,f0,f0,f0,m7,m8,f0,f0,q9,f0),A.z(!1,f0,f0,f0,f0,f0,m4,m5,f0,f0,m6,f0),A.z(!1,f0,f0,f0,f0,f0,ad1,ad2,f0,f0,r5,f0),A.z(!1,f0,f0,f0,f0,f0,ad3,f0,f0,f0,f0,k6)],n),"Focal entrapment of the posterior tibial nerve at the flexor retinaculum. Diagnosis is confirmed by the specific involvement of the medial and lateral plantar nerves (both sensory and motor) with sparing of proximal tibial muscles (Gastrocnemius), normal Achilles reflexes, and normal Sural SNAPs.",c1,"tarsal",c3,ae7,ae6,!0,c0,A.a(["Tarsal Tunnel Syndrome (TTS) involves compression of the posterior tibial nerve behind the medial malleolus.","Normal Sural and Superficial Fibular SNAPs help rule out more proximal lesions (Sciatic/Plexus) or generalized polyneuropathy.","Specialized plantar nerve studies (Mixed or Sensory) are necessary for diagnosis as standard Tibial motor studies may be normal early on."],af2),"Foot Numbness and Burning Pain")
ae6=A.cc(52,"Lower back pain radiating to posterior leg and lateral foot",i1,"4-month history of lower back pain following heavy lifting at work. Pain radiates down posterior aspect of right leg to lateral foot. Associated numbness in lateral foot and weakness in plantarflexion (toe walking). Pain worse with sitting and forward flexion.","Ibuprofen, gabapentin",r2,i4)
ae7=A.cg("Normal bulk. Patient unable to perform single-leg calf raise on the right.","Lumbar paraspinal tenderness.","Right Achilles reflex absent/diminished (0 or 1+). Patellar reflexes 2+ bilaterally.","Limited lumbar flexion.","Decreased sensation in S1 dermatome (lateral foot and small toe).","Positive straight leg raise at 45 degrees on right.","Right plantarflexion (Gastrocnemius) 4/5. Gluteus maximus 4/5. Other muscle groups 5/5.")
c3=A.a([A.V(ac9,d9),A.V(p8,"Sciatic lesions would typically involve peroneal muscles (TA, EHL) and the Sural SNAP; here those are entirely spared."),A.V(ad4,"A diagnosis of exclusion; would spare the paraspinal muscles and typically spares the S1 roots' contributions to the Gluteus Maximus (inferior gluteal nerve branches proximal to the piriformis)."),A.V(p9,"Plexopathy would involve multiple root levels (L5, S1, S2) and usually shows an abnormal Sural SNAP (post-ganglionic); here Sural is normal."),A.V(ad5,"primarily a pain syndrome without the neurologic deficits (absent reflex, abnormal EMG) seen here.")],ae8)
