c6=A.cd(ae2,c8,s2,"INDICATED (To confirm EDB involvement and spare TA/EHL)",A.a([A.z(!0,f0,f0,j8,f0,f0,"Extensor Digitorum Brevis (EDB)",t3,f0,h4,m1,f0),A.z(!1,"Spared (proximal to ankle)",f0,f0,f0,f0,l5,t3,f0,f0,q4,f0),A.z(!1,z0,f0,f0,f0,f0,m0,t3,f0,f0,q6,f0),A.z(!1,f0,f0,f0,f0,f0,m2,q7,f0,f0,m1,f0),A.z(!1,aa6,f0,f0,f0,f0,m4,m5,f0,f0,m6,f0),A.z(!1,aa6,f0,f0,f0,f0,m7,m8,f0,f0,m9,f0),A.z(!1,f0,f0,f0,f0,f0,n3,f0,f0,f0,f0,k6)],n),"Compression of the deep peroneal nerve under the extensor retinaculum. This localizes distal to the branches to the TA and EHL. The hallmark is isolated EDB atrophy/denervation and first webspace sensory loss with sparing of the proximal deep peroneal muscles (TA/EHL).",c7,ae1,c9,ae7,ae6,!0,c6,A.a(["Anterior Tarsal Tunnel Syndrome is an entrapment of the deep peroneal nerve at the ankle.","Localization Pearl: Isolated EDB denervation with Normal TA/EHL and Normal Superficial Fibular SNAP.","Commonly caused by tight-fitting footwear ('Cleat Palsy'), ankle trauma, or ganglion cysts.","Sensory loss is restricted to the first dorsal webspace (between the 1st and 2nd toes)."],af2),"Top of Foot Numbness and EDB Atrophy")
ae6=A.cc(41,"Aching pain in the right buttock that radiates down the back of the leg.",d5,"Symptoms began after starting a new exercise program involving heavy lunges. Pain is localized deep in the buttock and travels to the mid-calf. Worse with prolonged sitting and climbing stairs. Some numbness in the lateral foot. No back pain. No history of trauma.","Acetaminophen",u5,i4)
ae7=A.cg("Normal bulk. No visible asymmetry in the gluteal region.","Deep tenderness to palpation in the right sciatic notch. No lumbar paraspinal tenderness.","Right Achilles reflex 1+. Left Achilles reflex 2+. Patellar reflexes 2+ bilaterally.","Full hip ROM. Pain with internal rotation and adduction (FAIR test position).","Decreased sensation in the S1 distribution (lateral foot) and L5 distribution (dorsal foot).","Positive FAIR test (Flexion, Adduction, Internal Rotation). Negative straight leg raise for back pain, but reproduces buttock pain.","5/5 strength in the Gluteus Maximus (Hip extension). 4+/5 weakness in the hamstrings and ankle muscles (TA, EHL, Gastroc) on the right. Right ankle eversion is 4/5.")
c9=A.a([A.V(ad4,d9),A.V("S1 Radiculopathy (L5-S1 disc)","A radiculopathy would involve the S1 paraspinals and typically involves the Gluteus Maximus (Inferior Gluteal nerve, L5-S1-S2). Here, the gluteus maximus is spared and paraspinals are normal."),A.V("Sciatic Neuropathy (at the Notch)","Piriformis syndrome is a subset of sciatic neuropathy. Key localization is the exclusion of muscles innervated proximal to the piriformis (e.g., gluteals)."),A.V(ad9,"Causes lateral hip pain over the greater trochanter, but not radiating neurological symptoms or weak ankle reflection."),A.V(ad5,"Primarily causes SI joint pain; lacks the distal neurological deficits and denervation seen on EMG.")],ae8)
c7=A.a4(["constitutional","Negative.","musculoskeletal","Buttock and leg pain.","neurological","Radiating leg pain. No bowel/bladder changes."],af0,af0)
c8=A.a(["None."],af2)
c8=A.ce(A.a(["MRI Pelvis: Small area of edema in the right piriformis muscle; the sciatic nerve appears mildly hyperintense at the level of the sciatic notch."],af2),c8)
